This paper is about combining two tools for optimizing and analyzing floating-point computations. The paper discusses accuracy optimization and verification, which are both related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses program rewriting techniques, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of combining tools, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses bugs in the tools, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software testing and debugging (cs.SC).
